Dialogue: Marked=0,0:01:49.60,0:01:54.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The Shiver Of The Vampires
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:00.90,0:06:06.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, in a while I will return\nto the radiant darkness of death.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:08.60,0:06:13.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,But first, I want to give you\nthe means to save your lives...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:13.30,0:06:17.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,...and even a chance to save my soul.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:18.30,0:06:22.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Later tonight,\nas soon as death has taken me,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:22.10,0:06:24.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..I want you go to the cemetery.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:27.50,0:06:30.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, before it's too late.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:30.30,0:06:34.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Go to their tomb and drive\nthis stake into their hearts...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:34.20,0:06:37.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..so they are destroyed for ever.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:39.00,0:06:42.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Pull this stake from my heart\nand kill them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:42.60,0:06:47.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, if you are too late,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:47.10,0:06:49.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..swear that you will serve them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:49.80,0:06:52.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,That way your lives\nwill be spared.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:52.80,0:06:58.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They need living accomplices\nto supply them with victims.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:06:59.70,0:07:03.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Now let the light strike me down.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:10:32.40,0:10:35.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think it's a good place\nfor a honeymoon?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:10:35.50,0:10:39.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's a very beautiful castle,\nyou'll see.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:10:39.00,0:10:42.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I really want to see\nmy two cousins again.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:10:42.60,0:10:46.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I only saw them once or twice\nwhen I was a little girl...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:10:46.30,0:10:49.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..and I have wonderful\nmemories of it.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:10:49.40,0:10:51.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They're quite strange...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:10:51.60,0:10:56.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..but children are always\nfascinated by anything unusual.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:10:56.10,0:11:01.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to go, I just hope it\ndoesn't delay our trip to ltaly.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:11:34.50,0:11:38.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The castle is at the end\nof that lane...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:11:38.10,0:11:40.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..but you will find it empty.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:11:41.60,0:11:43.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Empty?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:11:43.70,0:11:46.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They both died yesterday.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:11:48.10,0:11:51.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You will only be able to see\ntheir two servants.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:11:51.80,0:11:55.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Strange things have been\nhappening here...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:11:55.30,0:11:58.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..since they're not here\nto protect us.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:11:58.50,0:12:00.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:12:00.60,0:12:02.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Go up to the castle. Go on!
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:12:14.80,0:12:18.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isle, do you know\nwhat I've just been told?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:12:18.40,0:12:21.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you won't be too upset but...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:12:21.40,0:12:24.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- What is it?\n- Your cousins are dead.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:12:24.80,0:12:26.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- Dead?\n- Yes.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:12:26.80,0:12:29.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They've not long been buried.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:12:29.40,0:12:32.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. Are you sure?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:12:32.20,0:12:34.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:12:35.60,0:12:37.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:15:30.50,0:15:36.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Hello. My cousins were expecting us.\nWe've just got married and...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:15:36.40,0:15:42.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,That explains our inappropriate\ndress but we had no way of knowing.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:15:42.20,0:15:46.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The occupants are delighted\nto welcome you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:15:46.10,0:15:48.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The rooms are ready,\nif you'd just follow us.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:16:49.50,0:16:52.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What a peculiar place.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:16:52.30,0:16:58.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be able to relax until I've\nvisited my cousins one last time.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:16:58.60,0:17:01.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to visit their tomb.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:17:01.20,0:17:03.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I really have to.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:17:03.30,0:17:06.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I feel I owe it to them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:17:08.20,0:17:10.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm going to go alone.\n- But why?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:17:10.90,0:17:13.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:18:37.50,0:18:40.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I'm lsabelle.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:18:41.40,0:18:44.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you praying at this tomb?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:18:44.20,0:18:47.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- Two men are buried here.\n- I know.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:18:47.00,0:18:49.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They were my last relatives.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:18:51.60,0:18:53.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Your dress is new.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:18:55.20,0:18:59.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Mine was worn by my mother\nwhen my father died.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:19:00.80,0:19:02.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,She died not long after.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:19:04.10,0:19:07.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm the one\nwearing the widow's veils.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:19:07.90,0:19:10.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Who for?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:19:10.40,0:19:12.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- For them.\n- For them?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:19:12.50,0:19:14.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We were to be married...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:19:14.60,0:19:17.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..but I was already their bride.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:19:17.50,0:19:19.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Whose bride?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:19:19.60,0:19:22.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows? Maybe both of them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:19:23.90,0:19:27.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Now I am mourning both of them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:19:27.90,0:19:30.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I have been twice widowed.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:20:38.00,0:20:42.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Antoine, let me sleep\nalone tonight, please.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:20:42.30,0:20:46.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,My cousins' deaths\nhave really upset me.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:20:46.30,0:20:51.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Please understand, Antoine.\nDon't be mad with me. Good night.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:20:52.40,0:20:54.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Good night.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:22:01.40,0:22:03.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:22:03.50,0:22:05.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I am Isolde.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:22:05.80,0:22:07.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You are Isle.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:23:50.90,0:23:52.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I am your friend.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:23:53.00,0:23:58.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I have some things to tell you,\nto explain to you, to show you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:24:38.40,0:24:43.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,This is where the living make\na religion of respecting the dead.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:24:43.60,0:24:48.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,This is where the dead make a\nreligion of preserving their lives.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:29:26.00,0:29:28.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Why, Master?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:29:28.10,0:29:30.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It has to be done.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:29:30.20,0:29:34.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The terrible curse which is ours\nmust not be passed on.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:29:34.90,0:29:36.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't she live, Master?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:29:36.40,0:29:39.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,She could,\nbut only as the dead live.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:29:39.70,0:29:42.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,She would have to share\nour eternity.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:29:42.70,0:29:47.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,She should never have entered\nthis sinister vault.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:29:47.20,0:29:50.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,This is the price we pay\nfor our safety.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:29:50.50,0:29:55.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Our evil should not be propagated,\nwe would be discovered.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:29:55.10,0:29:57.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Go and see\nif our hosts are resting.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:31:15.30,0:31:18.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What will happen to you\nnow you are here alone?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:31:18.80,0:31:23.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Loneliness does not trouble us\nwhen we are near our masters.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:31:24.00,0:31:25.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What about now they've left?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:31:25.50,0:31:30.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They haven't left us, they\nhaven't left anything or anyone.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:31:30.70,0:31:33.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The way you remember them\nis touching...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:31:33.90,0:31:38.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..but the fact is,\nwe will never see them again and...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:31:42.40,0:31:46.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We will see them once\ntheir work is finished.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:31:46.20,0:31:47.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,In the library.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:31:47.50,0:31:49.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:31:49.50,0:31:51.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What library?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:31:51.60,0:31:54.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't know what's going on.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:00.30,0:32:03.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,This is the time of day\nthey usually work.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:06.80,0:32:11.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They will come to see you\nwhen they are finished.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:15.70,0:32:17.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,So, they're alive?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:17.80,0:32:23.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,But we were told they were dead.\nIsle went to their tomb and now...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:23.50,0:32:24.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They could at least meet us.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:24.90,0:32:29.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What about lsabelle?\nShe thinks they're dead too.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:29.30,0:32:33.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,That's what people\nin the village are saying.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:34.50,0:32:38.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't pay\nattention to rumors.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:38.30,0:32:40.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Of course,\nit was them I saw last night.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:41.00,0:32:45.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- You saw them last night?\n- Don't you remember?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:45.10,0:32:46.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I was asleep.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:46.60,0:32:52.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, you weren't in your room so\nI went looking for you in the park.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:52.70,0:32:55.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I saw two men in a chapel.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:55.40,0:32:57.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The two servants were there.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:32:57.90,0:33:03.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Some sort of ceremony was being\ncarried out, a human sacrifice.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:33:03.60,0:33:06.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The two men were covered in blood.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:33:06.50,0:33:11.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I was afraid for you, I hurried back\nbut you were sound asleep.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:33:11.80,0:33:14.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was hallucinating.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:33:15.60,0:33:20.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if the lords are alive,\nI wonder...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:33:23.10,0:33:25.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to try to find them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:33:40.20,0:33:43.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They work during the day,\nin their library.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:37:51.10,0:37:53.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:37:53.20,0:37:55.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:37:55.20,0:37:57.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I went to look in the library.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:38:21.70,0:38:23.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Are they the men you saw?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:38:23.80,0:38:25.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That's them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:38:43.00,0:38:46.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,So this is our dear cousin.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:38:47.80,0:38:49.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,And our latest cousin.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:38:49.90,0:38:53.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Please excuse our late arrival.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:38:54.50,0:38:57.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but it's little Isle,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:38:58.20,0:39:00.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..so different now.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:03.00,0:39:05.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,And this must be Antoine.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:07.20,0:39:10.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,My dear Antoine,\nwhat happened to you?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:10.30,0:39:12.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,An unfortunate accident.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:13.90,0:39:16.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Old castles are dangerous.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:17.10,0:39:21.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Full of traps and mysteries,\nyou have to be very careful.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:21.50,0:39:23.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Very careful.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:33.10,0:39:36.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We were surprised\nto hear of your deaths.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:36.40,0:39:39.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Your reappearance\nis even more surprising.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:40.00,0:39:42.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We never disappeared.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:43.70,0:39:46.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,That's just a story, a joke.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:46.80,0:39:49.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Made up by the locals.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:49.30,0:39:53.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,lt's unbelievable.\nWhat kind of life do you lead?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:53.50,0:39:58.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,These days everything\nis unbelievable, my friend.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:39:58.10,0:40:00.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We lead the life we have to live.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:00.80,0:40:04.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What about you,\ndid you choose your life?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:04.20,0:40:08.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. In any case,\nmine doesn't seem so strange.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:08.20,0:40:11.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Appearances are deceptive.\nWhat do you do?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:11.50,0:40:13.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I am an electronics engineer.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:13.20,0:40:18.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Is it unbelievable to substitute\nan electronic brain for a man's?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:18.90,0:40:22.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's more than unbelievable,\nit's dangerous.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:22.80,0:40:25.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Our life is the result of our work.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:25.60,0:40:28.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It is related to our work.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:28.40,0:40:30.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What work?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:30.00,0:40:32.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Very important work.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:32.30,0:40:36.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We researched the historical\norigins of our family.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:36.50,0:40:39.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We've studied the religions...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:39.30,0:40:42.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..our family practised\nover the years.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:42.70,0:40:44.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We were lifted very high.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:44.80,0:40:47.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We were taken very low.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:47.50,0:40:52.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We discovered that the roots\nof our family go back...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:52.10,0:40:56.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..to very precise religions origins.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:56.10,0:40:59.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Which were of\ngreat scientific interest.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:40:59.70,0:41:03.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,That hardly seems\nto be scientific progress.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:03.70,0:41:08.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,If you ate instead of talking\nat least your meal would progress.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:08.60,0:41:12.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?\nYou're not eating very much.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:12.00,0:41:14.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, I wonder if you eat at all.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:14.80,0:41:16.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Antoine, really!
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:16.90,0:41:18.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Actually we do eat.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:19.00,0:41:21.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,But very little lately.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:21.30,0:41:24.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- But before...\n- Things were different.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:24.80,0:41:28.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,But what about\nthe research you carried out,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:29.00,0:41:34.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..you must have learned something\nimportant about your origins?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:34.40,0:41:39.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- We learned that our family...\n- Which we traced way back.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:39.50,0:41:43.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..significantly helped\nsome religions survive...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:43.60,0:41:45.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..at the end of the Middle Ages.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:45.50,0:41:48.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We're talking about\nthe worship of the goddess lsis.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:48.90,0:41:50.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You're egyptologists?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:51.00,0:41:55.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm mean the religion\nwhich continued in Europe...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:41:55.80,0:42:00.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..in spite of the persecution it\nsuffered from the Catholic church.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:00.90,0:42:06.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,That is why things were\nborrowed from foreign religions,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:06.70,0:42:10.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..as the goddess lsis was.\n- Who we already mentioned.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:10.40,0:42:14.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,In particular, Christians\nhunted down their enemies.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:14.40,0:42:19.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They adopted the ancient\nreligion of the horned god,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:19.30,0:42:22.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..who has been worshipped\nsince prehistory.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:22.20,0:42:26.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Violently persecuted,\nthis religion was destroyed.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:26.90,0:42:31.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Although they claimed\nto worship the goddess lsis,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:31.20,0:42:35.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..in fact, they had turned\na male god of local origin...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:35.80,0:42:39.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..into a female god\nof foreign origin.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:39.20,0:42:42.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,So those who opposed Christianity...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:42.20,0:42:46.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..adopted two arguments\nagainst their persecutors.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:46.60,0:42:50.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They'd say, ''We can't be blamed\nfor worshipping the horned god...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:50.50,0:42:52.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..because she is a woman.''
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:52.60,0:42:58.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes they'd say, ''She is a\nwoman, so we do not revere an idol.''
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:42:58.10,0:43:00.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,This woman was the Virgin Mary.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:43:00.50,0:43:06.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,As I said, it was all about derision\nbecause it was verging on blasphemy.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:43:06.80,0:43:11.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, it was all about\nblaspheming the Virgin Mary.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:43:11.40,0:43:16.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,With this notion of reversal,\nderision and blasphemy,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:43:16.50,0:43:19.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..we then take up\nthis reversal of rites...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:43:20.00,0:43:23.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..which was later\nto give us black masses.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:43:23.70,0:43:27.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The worship of the dear lsis...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:43:27.10,0:43:32.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..is at the very heart of\nthe Western crisis at that time.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:43:32.20,0:43:35.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It is also at the heart,\nthe very heart...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:43:36.00,0:43:38.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..of our research.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:45:38.00,0:45:40.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We're alone at last.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:45:40.10,0:45:44.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Please,\nlet me be alone again tonight.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:45:44.00,0:45:49.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We're alone. Your cousins are\nweird, don't take them seriously.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:45:49.70,0:45:54.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- Please.\n- I've had enough of your..
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:45:54.50,0:45:59.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get upset, you just said\nnot to take them seriously.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:45:59.50,0:46:01.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- They are intelligent.\n- lntelligent but crazy.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:46:01.80,0:46:04.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not hanging around here.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:48:38.00,0:48:40.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's nine o'clock.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:48:40.10,0:48:42.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I remember.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:48:42.20,0:48:45.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They always went out at this time.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:48:46.30,0:48:49.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They used to send Anubis,\ntheir dog, to fetch me.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:48:50.50,0:48:52.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They went out hunting.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:48:52.80,0:48:55.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They hunted at night, like wolves.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:48:56.50,0:48:58.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They were so cheerful.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:48:59.50,0:49:03.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes I'd slip away\nand go with them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:49:03.80,0:49:06.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't have understood.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:49:06.30,0:49:10.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They hunted their dreadful prey\nwith stakes.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:49:11.30,0:49:15.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They carried holy scapulars\nand crosses.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:49:17.00,0:49:21.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They looked like two lords from\nthe ancient era of the crusades.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:49:21.80,0:49:27.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They'd return covered in blood\nand drunk from the battle.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:49:27.40,0:49:33.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,But one day they returned\nwith wounds on their necks.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:49:34.90,0:49:39.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They had what looked like bites\nwhich were bleeding.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:49:41.60,0:49:43.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Bleeding...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:49:43.70,0:49:46.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They bled to death.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:50:11.70,0:50:13.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's Anubis, their dog.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:50:13.90,0:50:16.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,He's calling me.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:50:33.80,0:50:35.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:50:35.90,0:50:38.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you bring me here?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:50:39.20,0:50:41.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Did you send Anubis to me?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:50:41.60,0:50:43.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What do you know?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:50:45.50,0:50:50.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, I know that Anubis\nused to bark under your window...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:50:50.90,0:50:53.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..when your lovers\nwished to see you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:50:53.90,0:50:59.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You hounded the two masters of\nthe castle with your selfish love.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:50:59.30,0:51:02.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,That will have to stop immediately.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:02.90,0:51:06.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The lords have been dead\nfor several days...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:06.80,0:51:11.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..and my love for them\nonly troubles me now.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:11.40,0:51:13.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Turn around.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:13.50,0:51:18.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,One moment.\nYou are no longer welcome here.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:18.00,0:51:23.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot deal with what I am\nor what they are now.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:24.50,0:51:26.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:26.60,0:51:29.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What's happened to you?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:29.10,0:51:31.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I loved you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:31.20,0:51:33.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Remember?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:33.30,0:51:35.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You were men when I loved you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:37.20,0:51:39.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Look at you now.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:51:40.40,0:51:43.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you obey this creature?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:52:42.30,0:52:48.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,That was good. You adopted the only\nbehaviour that was appropriate,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:52:48.30,0:52:50.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..silence.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:52:50.40,0:52:53.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,She was the last connection\nwith our former life.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:52:54.00,0:52:57.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We are now free. Free...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:52:57.50,0:52:59.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..never to die again.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:52:59.60,0:53:02.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We are free never to live again.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:02.30,0:53:06.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You have forgotten something else\nabout your past.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:07.00,0:53:09.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isle.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:09.50,0:53:15.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You mean to say you're going\nto kill poor Isle too.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:15.10,0:53:17.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:17.20,0:53:20.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I seduced her. It's taken care of.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:21.90,0:53:24.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Would it matter to you?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:24.00,0:53:28.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,He have to turn her into one\nof our own race, your own race.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:28.90,0:53:31.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough! Don't be insolent.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:31.30,0:53:33.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Her name is Isle,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:33.40,0:53:37.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..she was predestined for it,\njust like you were.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:37.70,0:53:42.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I implore you, Isolde,\ndon't rub salt into the wound.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:42.30,0:53:44.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:44.40,0:53:46.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You have not yet forgotten...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:46.90,0:53:50.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..that not long ago\nyou were vampire slayers.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:50.50,0:53:55.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't stop you becoming\nvampires because it was your fate.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:53:55.90,0:54:00.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It was an accident.\nIf this monster hadn't bitten us...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:00.10,0:54:01.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you calling a monster?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:02.80,0:54:06.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think this is\nan ideal situation for us?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:07.20,0:54:12.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Our body requires that we satisfy\nour most beastly appetites...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:12.40,0:54:17.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..whilst our lucid spirits\nwish to fight against them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:17.20,0:54:21.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,And, above all, fight\nagainst your atrocious revenge.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:21.10,0:54:23.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I'm proud of the way I am.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:23.20,0:54:27.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate my position\nas a wandering vampire.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:27.50,0:54:31.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It is an honour,\na very important privilege.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:33.00,0:54:36.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The master of the world sends me\nwhere I can be of use.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:36.90,0:54:43.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Without me, the monster, as you call\nhim, would never have infected you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:43.10,0:54:48.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I remember that your sudden\nappearance that night paralyzed us.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:54:51.20,0:54:56.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The same way my gaze paralyzed Isle\nand placed her at my mercy.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:00.10,0:55:02.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- Why us?\n- Yes, why us?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:02.20,0:55:04.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I will remind you again.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:04.30,0:55:06.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It was your destiny.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:07.80,0:55:11.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,In antiquity, this region\nwas a kingdom of vampires.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:12.00,0:55:14.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,There are many in the world.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:14.40,0:55:17.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Even your research\nbrought you to us.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:17.80,0:55:21.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing in life happens by chance.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:21.20,0:55:23.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's outrageous.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:23.30,0:55:25.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't. You're still at home,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:26.00,0:55:30.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..you have your own tombs\nto escape the light of day,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:30.20,0:55:32.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..devoted servants.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:32.30,0:55:34.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You're bourgeois vampires.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:42.50,0:55:45.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't we the same as you?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:45.80,0:55:51.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You're a wandering vampire and\nwe're bourgeois vampires, you say?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:51.70,0:55:53.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,My parents were both vampires...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:53.70,0:55:57.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..who were able to give me\neternal life.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:55:57.20,0:56:02.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,When I was born, the master of the\nworld invested them as initiates.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:04.40,0:56:10.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,In short, you killed Isabelle,\nwho could have given us a child,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:10.20,0:56:15.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..so we couldn't become initiates,\nmaking us your superiors.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:18.30,0:56:21.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isabelle loved you\nbecause you hunted vampires,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:21.90,0:56:24.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..she'd never accept you like this.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:24.60,0:56:26.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What do you know?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:26.70,0:56:31.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you try to seduce\nIsabelle like you did Isle?
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:31.30,0:56:35.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You had made her a woman.\nShe was too set in her ways.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:35.70,0:56:41.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You gave her a joyous life\nin that village.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:42.10,0:56:45.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll give you Isle\nto console you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:45.30,0:56:48.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,She is all ready.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:49.20,0:56:53.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You are just as desirable\nas Isabelle, Isolde.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:56:56.10,0:57:00.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,And we are still masters\nof this faraway village.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:57:00.00,0:57:03.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We could both take you,\njust like we took lsabelle.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:57:04.60,0:57:06.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:57:06.30,0:57:09.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it! I hate men. I hate them!
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:57:16.50,0:57:18.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:57:20.90,0:57:23.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,No! Leave me alone.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:58:42.90,0:58:47.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Who is going to wake him and how?\nHe must wake up naturally.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:58:48.70,0:58:53.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We'll wake him gently.\nOne of us will slip next to him.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:58:53.30,0:58:55.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,He's had a long period\nof abstinence.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:58:55.60,0:58:58.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We need to awaken his desire\nso he'll open his eyes.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:58:58.90,0:59:01.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- You do it.\n- You do it.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:59:01.00,0:59:02.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- No, you.\n- No, you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,0:59:02.90,0:59:05.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We'll both have to do it.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:02:38.30,1:02:40.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Where are they?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:02:41.40,1:02:43.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going mad. Isle!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:02:53.50,1:02:57.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really know\nwhat I saw, or thought I saw,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:02:57.30,1:03:00.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..but I know these\npeople are dangerous.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:03:00.80,1:03:02.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We must leave straight away.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:03:02.60,1:03:07.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not possible.\nI feel weak. I need peace and rest.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:03:07.50,1:03:09.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You won't get any rest here.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:03:09.50,1:03:13.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you, I'll even carry you,\nbut we must go.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:03:13.30,1:03:17.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand. I love\nmy cousins, they're my only family.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:03:17.70,1:03:19.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd lost them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:03:19.80,1:03:23.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Your only family... What about me?\nI'm your husband.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:03:24.00,1:03:28.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Of course you are, Antoine,\nbut it's not the same.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:03:28.10,1:03:31.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,In any case,\nyou aren't truly my husband yet.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:03:32.00,1:03:33.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Is that my fault?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:03:33.80,1:03:37.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,OK, if that's the way it is,\nI'll stay.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:04:42.40,1:04:44.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isle, what's the matter?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:04:44.50,1:04:46.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's the window, the light.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:04:46.60,1:04:49.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:04:49.10,1:04:50.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The daylight hurts my eyes.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:04:51.00,1:04:56.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You're not awake yet. Let's go out,\nthe fresh air will do you good.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:05:24.70,1:05:28.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You've changed\nsince we've been here.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:05:30.80,1:05:33.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You seem distant,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:05:35.60,1:05:37.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..lost.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:05:37.60,1:05:39.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isolde.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:05:39.30,1:05:41.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:05:41.40,1:05:43.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isolde.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:05:43.30,1:05:45.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isolde?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:05:45.40,1:05:51.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's the name of that woman who took\nyou to that ceremony, isn't it?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:05:51.10,1:05:53.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,So I wasn't dreaming.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:06:42.90,1:06:46.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it! Leave it alone.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:06:46.60,1:06:49.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening?\nWhat's the matter?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:06:49.70,1:06:51.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ill?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:06:51.80,1:06:54.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's nothing. I'm alright.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:06:54.70,1:06:56.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The daylight hurts my eyes.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:06:57.00,1:06:59.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The daylight hurts your eyes?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:06:59.60,1:07:03.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Go and fetch my sunglasses\nfrom the car, please.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:09:02.60,1:09:04.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't open it.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:09:04.70,1:09:07.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The daylight will kill me.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:09:12.80,1:09:16.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The blood that you spilled near\nto me woke me before time.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:09:17.00,1:09:22.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,If my eyes were to see the daylight\nit would kill me.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:09:43.10,1:09:47.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isle, I can feel you are hesitating,\nare you going to open it?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:09:47.90,1:09:50.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What will you decide?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:09:50.20,1:09:52.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:09:52.20,1:09:54.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what to do.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:09:54.30,1:09:57.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really know who you are.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:09:57.00,1:09:59.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Or even who I am.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:10:03.30,1:10:09.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I belong to the world of darkness\nwhose eternal joys will be yours.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:10:09.00,1:10:12.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Your cousins and I\nare messengers down here.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:10:12.50,1:10:18.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,If you spare me, you will become\none of us and others like us.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:10:18.10,1:10:21.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,If, on the other hand,\nyou open this coffin...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:10:21.70,1:10:25.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..you will be left alone\nin this world...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:10:25.00,1:10:29.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..to carry the weight\nof an unbearable mortality.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:11:01.10,1:11:05.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Take me back to my room,\nI'll feel better tonight.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:12:55.40,1:12:58.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm too weary to walk.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:12:58.70,1:13:04.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong to be afraid of my\ncousins, they don't mean any harm.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:13:04.40,1:13:06.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I love them.\nI love all three of them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:15:48.00,1:15:50.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Quick, we must get out of here.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:15:50.50,1:15:52.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Why? What happened?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:15:52.60,1:15:55.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They are vampires, both of them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:15:55.40,1:15:58.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I saw them,\nthey were drinking blood.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:15:58.60,1:16:01.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We must leave\nwhile we're still alive.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:16:01.60,1:16:05.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They are alive,\nand will be so eternally.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:16:05.30,1:16:07.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,What? What are you saying?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:16:07.60,1:16:10.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you dressed like that?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:16:10.20,1:16:12.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,There is a wedding today.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:16:13.30,1:16:17.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The ceremony which will make me\nthe same as lsolde...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:16:17.40,1:16:19.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..and my two companions.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:16:19.50,1:16:23.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isle, I don't recognize you.\nWho is lsolde?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:16:23.30,1:16:26.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You will see her, any time now.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:16:26.20,1:16:28.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's time.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:16:32.10,1:16:34.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,How will she appear?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:16:36.00,1:16:38.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,From where will she arise?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:17:16.50,1:17:19.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,This is Isolde, she is my friend.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:17:26.20,1:17:27.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:17.40,1:18:19.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You seem anxious, Antoine.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:19.90,1:18:22.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Why is the table only set for one?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:22.20,1:18:25.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isle fears the light,\ncan't she eat now?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:25.70,1:18:27.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- Food?\n- Food.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:27.20,1:18:32.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,As you are aware, we need just\na small diet, from time to time.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:32.40,1:18:36.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,A little diet\nhas never hurt any woman.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:36.50,1:18:39.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,As for her fear of daylight, well...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:39.60,1:18:44.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It is photophobia.\nIt's quite common.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:44.30,1:18:46.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite normal.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:46.70,1:18:50.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,And it is recognized\nby psychiatrists.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:50.10,1:18:52.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,All it takes is a slight imbalance.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:52.80,1:18:55.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Slightly high blood pressure.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:55.50,1:18:57.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,A little bit of tiredness.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:18:57.80,1:19:00.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Take me for example, often I...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:19:00.50,1:19:06.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The slightest psychological disorder\nand photophobia occurs.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:19:09.70,1:19:11.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You needn't worry.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:19:11.80,1:19:13.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite normal.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:19:13.90,1:19:19.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say the fear of sunlight\nis just as normal as...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:19:19.30,1:19:21.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The fear of God.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:19:21.40,1:19:27.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Sunlight, I say,\nis the beginning of lunar...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:19:27.30,1:19:29.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..wisdom.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:19:29.40,1:19:35.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The wisdom that was our ancestors',\ngreat admirers of the night sky.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:19:35.30,1:19:38.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Direct ancestors\nof us and our cousin.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:19:38.40,1:19:40.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Direct ancestors.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:08.20,1:20:10.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Get rid of that crucifix!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:12.60,1:20:14.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Grab him.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:14.70,1:20:16.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Fetch the ropes!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:18.30,1:20:20.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I've got him.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:27.30,1:20:29.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isle, you betrayed me.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:29.80,1:20:31.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isle!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:31.90,1:20:35.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They'll turn you into a monstrous\nvampire. lt's inadmissible.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:35.50,1:20:38.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,But everything is admissible.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:38.40,1:20:41.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We are just as admissible as you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:41.00,1:20:44.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Despite all the differences\nbetween us.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:44.60,1:20:49.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We understand that these differences\nmight shock you at first.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:49.40,1:20:54.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,If we're so different\nwhy can't you leave us alone?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:54.40,1:20:56.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You've touched a sore point.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:56.90,1:20:59.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,A sore point for Isle and me!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:20:59.30,1:21:01.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,A sore point for us, believe me.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:02.00,1:21:06.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think that\nwe have always been this way.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:06.70,1:21:09.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care what you were like!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:09.30,1:21:12.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Very well,\nbut you are making a mistake.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:12.70,1:21:16.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- It will help you understand.\n- To understand us.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:16.10,1:21:21.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It will help you understand\nthe situation we're all in today.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:21.40,1:21:23.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,You and us.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:23.20,1:21:27.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,ln brief,\nthe research we spoke of earlier...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:27.10,1:21:30.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Took us from one religion\nto another.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:30.10,1:21:32.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Each one more underground.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:32.30,1:21:35.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Until we came\nto the most underground of all.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:35.50,1:21:42.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,And not just a religion but also\na symptom of the human state.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:42.30,1:21:45.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,If the word human still\napplies to our host.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:45.30,1:21:50.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,In short, we were lead\ninto contact with vampirism.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:50.10,1:21:55.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,That first contact wasn't exactly\nto the vampires' liking...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:55.10,1:21:58.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..because we were\ntheir sworn enemies.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:21:58.50,1:22:01.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I think we were the most fearsome...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:01.10,1:22:06.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..and extraordinary vampire hunters\nin the whole universe.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:06.50,1:22:07.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Our tally was impressive.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:08.00,1:22:11.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- That's right.\n- Fantastic.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:11.60,1:22:13.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Until the day...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:13.60,1:22:16.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Until the day a unfortunate event...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:16.40,1:22:19.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,- An accident.\n- A appalling accident.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:19.70,1:22:21.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, appalling.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:21.80,1:22:25.50,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,They contaminated us\nand made us what we are today.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:25.60,1:22:28.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,And so what choice did we have?
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:28.20,1:22:30.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We could only accept our new duties.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:31.00,1:22:33.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,And we accepted them.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:33.10,1:22:35.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Completely.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:35.80,1:22:42.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,So maybe now you can understand, my\ndear, in light of our sad story,...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:22:42.60,1:22:47.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..that our fate is also worthy\nof some compassion.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:23:04.30,1:23:08.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,The initiation ceremony\nwill take place tonight.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:23:08.40,1:23:10.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isle.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:23:10.50,1:23:12.20,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Our Isle...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:23:12.30,1:23:16.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..will receive the final kiss,\nthe final bite...
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:23:16.80,1:23:19.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,..which will allow her to join us.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:24:10.40,1:24:13.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Those monsters terrorize you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:24:13.30,1:24:17.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,l can set you free tonight\nand give you back your freedom.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:27:52.30,1:27:54.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Open the gate! Let me out!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:27:54.80,1:27:56.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Take that crucifix away.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:27:57.00,1:27:59.10,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Let me out, I will die.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:27:59.20,1:28:01.30,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Let me out!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:28:02.30,1:28:04.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Let me out!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:28:04.40,1:28:06.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Let me out!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:28:06.50,1:28:09.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Let me out! Help me.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:28:10.90,1:28:12.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Help me!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:31:00.50,1:31:02.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It will soon be light.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:31:04.60,1:31:06.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to go back.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:31:06.70,1:31:08.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,We're staying here.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:31:33.90,1:31:38.00,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's not too late,\nI can still save you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:33:54.30,1:33:56.40,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Come back!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:34:03.50,1:34:05.60,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isle, I love you.
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:34:06.60,1:34:08.70,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Come back!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:34:16.50,1:34:18.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,Isle, come back. I love you!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:34:33.80,1:34:35.80,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,No, Isle!
Dialogue: Marked=0,1:34:47.60,1:34:50.90,NORMAL,00,0000,0000,0000,,I love you, Isle!

